{"article_id":"a8y6hgoyGMKOblAj","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON ( ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The White House said on Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"it was searching for ways","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"to unilaterally fund the building of a controversial wall on the U.S.-Mexico border","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"that Congress is balking at ,","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"possibly easing chances of a government shutdown this weekend .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders told reporters","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"President Donald Trump has asked his Cabinet agencies to \" look","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"and see","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"if they have money","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"that can be used \"","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"to begin building the wall .","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"Previously , Trump had demanded","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that Congress approve $ 5 billion in new funds for the wall","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"he argues","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"is needed","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"to stop illegal immigrants and drugs from entering through the southwest border .","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"On Tuesday , Trump said","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"it was too early to say","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"whether a partial government shutdown will be averted by a Friday midnight deadline","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"when existing funds for several agencies expire .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"\" We ' ll see what happens , \"","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"he told reporters .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"But some Republican senators said","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"they thought","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"the president could be persuaded to sign a bill","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"that does not fund his wall ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"and several Republican and Democratic senators spoke of the possibility of a stop-gap funding bill","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"passing this week","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"that would simply extend government operations into the new year .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"The new Congress","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"that convenes on Jan. 3","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"would then have to grapple with the budget impasse .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Given the continued uncertainty , however ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"federal agencies began publicizing their plans in case of a partial government shutdown .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"The State Department , for example , said","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"its consular operations , both domestic and abroad , would continue","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"\" as long as there are sufficient fees","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"to support operations. \"","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"However , passport agencies might not operate","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"if they are located in government buildings","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"affected by the lapse in appropriations .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"Earlier on Tuesday , Trump and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell had proposed a plan","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"that would have had Congress approve $ 1 billion in unspecified money","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"that Trump could use","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"to advance his border security priorities .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer called it a \" slush fund \"","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"that was promptly rejected .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"Democrats , along with some Republicans , oppose the wall as a costly , ineffective border security tool .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"Even some Republicans balked at the $ 1 billion fund .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"\" I ' m not sure","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"I would insist on that , \"","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Senator Roger Wicker told reporters .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Republican Senator Marco Rubio ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"referring to the prospects of a bill","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"to extend current spending for a short period , such as a few weeks","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"\" might be the only route forward","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"considering the time constraints","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"we face. \"","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Schumer said","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Democrats would \" very seriously consider \" such a move .","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"Congress has been trying to approve around $ 450 billion in funds","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"to keep a variety of federal agencies operating beyond Friday .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Included is the Department of Homeland Security ,","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"which is responsible for border security .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Failure","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"to agree to new appropriations by that deadline could leave about a quarter of the federal workforce without paychecks","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"and some federal programs shuttered","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"until the impasse is resolved .","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"Trump has demanded $ 5 billion as a down payment on construction of a wall ,","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"which was a key pledge of his 2016 presidential campaign .","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"Trump originally said","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Mexico would pay for the wall ,","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"but Mexico has refused .","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"It was unclear whether any Cabinet heads , such as Defense Secretary James Mattis , would find money in their existing accounts","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"to funnel to a wall ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"or whether they even had the authority","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"to do so .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":157,"left":0,"right":156,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":139,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":120,"right":138,"relation":"elaborat